headline.main: R.A.F. SAYS 'COBRA' INSURES AIR EDGE; Pilot Thinks U.S.-Built Plane Will Prove Superior to the Messerschmitt 109-Fs FLIES 400 MILES AN HOUR Machine Mounts One Cannon, 6 Other Guns -- Americans Aid in Training Unit

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Oct. 17 -- The Royal Air Force has something new in store for the German Air Force's much vaunted Messerschmitt 109-F plane, it was learned today. It is the American-built Airacobra fighter machine, one of the most advanced airplanes of its kind anywhere in the world at present.
abstract: Amers aid in training RAF in Airacobra plane use; data on RAF pilot standards
